    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed or appropriately scoped out at Model Risk Level 2. The neural network surrogate achieves R² = 0.974 and RMSE = 0.0031 on the held-out test set, exceeding all pre-specified acceptance thresholds. Worst-case operating condition identification agrees with full CFD in 97.9% of test geometries, satisfying the RH < 1 regulatory acceptance criterion. The credibility assessment team concludes that the surrogate model provides sufficient evidence of credibility to support the regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device.",
